20/01/2006
CANBERRA, Australia -- Authorities have arrested former Serb militia commander Dragan Vasiljkovic, who is accused of torturing and killing Croat soldiers and civilians in rebel Serb-held territories during the 1991-1995 conflict. Australian Attorney General Philip Ruddock announced the arrest on Friday (20 January). Vasiljkovic, 51, was picked up in Sydney on a Croatian warrant. He has dual citizenship and was working as a golf instructor in Perth. Croatia will have 60 days to file an official request for his extradition. A judge has ordered his continued detention pending extradition hearings. (Reuters, AP, BBC - 20/01/06)
